","1598–1629":"1598–1629","1599–1662":"1599–1662","1571–1607":"1571–1607","16 July 1599":"16 July 1599","1571":"1571","1593":"1593","1600":"1600","1567":"1567","1599":"1599","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1630":"1630","1585":"1585","1662":"1662","about 1598":"about 1598","1607":"1607","1629":"1629","1617":"1617","before about 1607":"before about 1607","about 1592":"about 1592","about 1571":"about 1571","about 1593":"about 1593","Harberton, Devon, England":"Harberton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Burt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (southern): variant of   Bird  ,   Bright  , or   Burd  .","German: Middle High German <i>burt</i> ‘that which is due or proper’, therefore a nickname for someone who has fulfilled his obligations properly.","Jewish (from Poland and Ukraine): variant of   Burd  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bird","meanings":["English and Scottish: nickname for a young or a small and slender person, from Middle English <i>brid</i>, <i>bird</i>, <i>burd</i> (Old English <i>bird</i>, <i>brid</i>, perhaps also <i>byrd</i>) ‘bird, young bird’, also ‘young man, young woman, child’.","Irish: Anglicized form of a number of Irish names erroneously thought to contain the element <i>éan</i> ‘bird’, in particular <i>Ó hÉinigh</i> (see   Heagney  ), <i>Ó hÉanna</i> (see   Heaney  ), <i>Ó hÉanacháin</i> (see   Heneghan  ), and <i>Mac an Déaghanaigh</i> (see   McEneaney  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames meaning ‘bird’, as for example German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Vogel  , French   Loiseau  , Czech <b>Ptáček</b> (see   Ptacek  ) and <b>Pták</b>, Polish   Ptak  ."]},{"name":"Birt","meanings":["English (Gloucestershire): variant of   Burt  .","German: habitational name from any of several places in the Rhineland named Birth or Birten.","In some cases also Croatian: occupational name from <i>birt</i> ‘inn-keeper’, a regional or colloquial word of German origin (see   Wirt  )."]},{"name":"Burtt","meanings":["English: variant of   Burt  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705206,"age":0,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":14,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":16,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705210,"age":29,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Henry Burt was born about 1571, in Devon, England. She married Henry Burt about 1592. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters. She died before about 1607."},"et":{"about 1571–before about 1607":"umbes 1571–umbes enne 1607","1567–1617":"1567–1617","1593–Male":"1593–Surnud","1597–1630":"1597–1630","1598–1617":"1598–1617","1598–1629":"1598–1629","1599–1662":"1599–1662","1571–1607":"1571–1607","16 July 1599":"16. juuli 1599","1571":"1571","1593":"1593","1600":"1600","1567":"1567","1599":"1599","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1630":"1630","1585":"1585","1662":"1662","about 1598":"umbes 1598","1607":"1607","1629":"1629","1617":"1617","before about 1607":"umbes enne 1607","about 1592":"umbes 1592","about 1571":"umbes 1571","about 1593":"umbes 1593","Harberton, Devon, England":"Harberton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1571–before about 1607":"noin 1571–ennen vuotta noin 1607","1567–1617":"1567–1617","1593–Male":"1593–Kuollut","1597–1630":"1597–1630","1598–1617":"1598–1617","1598–1629":"1598–1629","1599–1662":"1599–1662","1571–1607":"1571–1607","16 July 1599":"16. heinäkuuta 1599","1571":"1571","1593":"1593","1600":"1600","1567":"1567","1599":"1599","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1630":"1630","1585":"1585","1662":"1662","about 1598":"noin 1598","1607":"1607","1629":"1629","1617":"1617","before about 1607":"ennen vuotta noin 1607","about 1592":"noin 1592","about 1571":"noin 1571","about 1593":"noin 1593","Harberton, Devon, England":"Harberton, 